cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its results, please cite the paper below."
title: "gcd-authz: Grammar-Constrained Decoding as a Positive Authorization Control for LLM Agents"
abstract: >-
  A self-contained, fully local experiment porting Galloway (2020),
  "Application Whitelisting as a Malicious Code Protection Control," into the
  LLM-agent domain: behavioral guardrails (the negative control) versus
  Grammar-Constrained Decoding with a per-request authorization grammar (the
  positive control), measured over millions of attack trials on the Tantalus
  CTF agent across three model lineages.
type: software
authors:
